  <sect2 role="installation">
    <title>Installation of syslinux</title>

    <para>First, apply a patch which removes dependency on the Perl
    package:</para>

<screen><userinput remap="pre">patch -p1 -i ../&syslinux-no_perl-patch;</userinput></screen>

    <para>Compile the package:</para>

<screen><userinput remap="make">cc extlinux-bin2c-replacement.c -o libinstaller/bin2c.pl
PATH="$PATH:$PWD/libinstaller" make -C libinstaller PERL=""
make -C extlinux
make -C linux</userinput></screen>

    <para>Install the package:</para>

<screen><userinput remap="install">install -v extlinux/extlinux linux/syslinux /bin
install -v -D -m 644 mbr/mbr.bin /lib/syslinux/mbr.bin
install -v -m 644 man/extlinux.1 man/syslinux.1 /usr/share/man/man1</userinput></screen>

  <para>Using syslinux to make your LFS system bootable will be discussed in
  <xref linkend="ch-bootable-syslinux"/>.</para>

  </sect2>

